OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777889102
OL,3,C5G mast set on fire in Oxford
OL,5,FThames Valley Police are appealing for
OL,6,Fwitnesses following an arson attack in
OL,7,FOxford in which a 5G mast was set on
OL,8,Ffire.
OL,10,FThe attack happened between 11.10pm -
OL,11,F11.35pm on Wednesday (29th May.) The
OL,12,F5G mast is close to the dual
OL,13,Fcarriageway of the Eastern Bypass,
OL,14,Fnear to the Rosehill and Littlemore
OL,15,Froundabout and Sandy Lane West.
OL,17,FNo one was injured during this
OL,18,Fincident.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/3
